    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01/48b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-08T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 8, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. We are sorry that the British will not join us in recognizing the
                    Administration of President Barclay under present conditions. <pb facs="1051"
                        n="949" xml:id="pg_949"/> We continue to believe that the Kru problem is
                    only one part of a larger problem; that Barclay’s reform plan provides for the
                    reorganization of native administration under a foreign specialist who can take
                    up the Kru question; and finally that further non-recognition would raise an
                    insurmountable barrier which would prevent us from effectively assisting in the
                    development of President Barclay’s plans whenever such assistance might be
                    requested. We are accordingly directing Hibbard to extend formal recognition on
                    Tuesday, June 11th. Please informally bring the foregoing to the attention of
                    the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
